ProtoResult:
. "A function $f$ has a limit at $x_0$ if and only if it has 
   left- and right-hand limits at $x_0$ and they are equal. 
   More specifically, $$ \lim_{x\to x_0} f(x)=L $$ if and only 
   if $$ f(x_0+)=f(x_0-)=L. $$"
